= GitHub Repository Access Guide

This guide explains how to access, fork, and contribute to the RAG repository.

== Clone the Repository

[source,bash]
----
# Clone without authentication (read-only)
git clone https://github.com/bniladridas/rag.git
cd rag
----

[source,bash]
----
# Or clone with SSH (requires SSH key)
git clone git@github.com:bniladridas/rag.git
cd rag
----

== Fork the Repository

. Go to https://github.com/bniladridas/rag
. Click the *Fork* button (top right)
. Select your GitHub account
. Clone your fork:

[source,bash]
----
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/rag.git
cd rag
----

== Set Up Remote

[source,bash]
----
# Add original repo as upstream
git remote add upstream https://github.com/bniladridas/rag.git

# Verify
git remote -v
# origin    https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/rag.git (fetch)
# origin    https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/rag.git (push)
# upstream  https://github.com/bniladridas/rag.git (fetch)
# upstream  https://github.com/bniladridas/rag.git (push)
----

== Create a Feature Branch

[source,bash]
----
# Update your fork
git fetch upstream
git checkout main
git merge upstream/main

# Create a new branch
git checkout -b feature/my-new-feature
----

== Make Changes and Commit

[source,bash]
----
# Make your changes, then stage and commit
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add new feature"
----

== Push and Create Pull Request

[source,bash]
----
# Push to your fork
git push origin feature/my-new-feature
----

. Go to your fork on GitHub
. Click *Compare & pull request*
. Fill in the PR description
. Click *Create pull request*

== Keep Your Fork Updated

[source,bash]
----
# Fetch and merge from upstream
git fetch upstream
git checkout main
git merge upstream/main
git push origin main
----

== GitHub CLI

[source,bash]
----
# Install gh CLI
brew install gh

# Authenticate
gh auth login

# Clone using gh
gh repo clone bniladridas/rag

# Create PR
gh pr create --title "My PR" --body "Description"
----
